A judge has ruled that Google has a monopoly on online search because it paid partners to make its search engine the default on phones and mobile browsers. But you don‚Äôt have to use Google, and there are many reasons not to. Alternative search engines often give you more privacy and sometimes come with other benefits as well, such as rewards or donations to worthy causes based on how much you search. The quality of results between Google and other search engines used to be a real issue, but now you‚Äôd be hard-pressed to find much difference: DuckDuckGo, Bing, AOL, ChatGPT and Brave Search to name a few.
